FAO Decorates Brazilian First Lady
BRASILIA , February 26 ( Xinhua ) -- The United Nations Food and Agriculture Organization ( FAO ) awarded the " Ceres " Medal to Brazil 's First Lady Ruth Cardoso for her contribution to the war against poverty in Brazil .
During a special ceremony held at the presidential palace , FAO Director-General Jacques Diouf pinned the decoration on Mrs. Cardoso .
He praised her work at the head of Brazil 's Solidarity Community in the war against poverty .
The FAO Ceres Medal is awarded only to distinguished women .
The late Mother Teresa , the late Indian Prime Minister Indira Gandhi and Thai Queen Sirikit Kittiyakara have won the award .
